"25.4oz bottle. Pours a murky orange-ish brown colot with a 1/4 inch of head. Some lacing. The aroma is bready with apricots, peaches, honey, and caramel. The taste is wheat, peaches, apricots, honey, and some toasted malts. Some floral hops as well. Finishes with more wheat, honey, and apricots. Fairly noticeable alcohol presence. Lightly carbonated. Fruity and bready with a fair amount of sweetness. Overall, not bad but nothing I need to have again."
