"Poured into a Fremont small snifter.  Pous a hazy, medium orange amber with a brief thin head that dissipates to light ring around the glass, leaving no lacing. Aroma of caramel, light stone fruit, alcohol. Flavor is sweet wheat, caramel, honey, stone fruit, finishes unexpectedly dry and peppery with lingering hop bitterness. Thick, almost syrupy body with light carbonation. A classic take on a wheatwine, with the sweet body and hop finish, a bit sweeter than expected, but the drier finish balances that out and make an interesting flavor progression. I'm curious about how this one would age as the sweetness balances out; will cellar one if I see another bottle."
